---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ProductCard from '../components/ProductCard.astro';

const products = [
  {
    name: 'LCARS-fleet',
    subtitle: 'Lightweight Contained Agent Resilient System',
    tagline:
      'Multi-agent fleet runtime for Claude Code. ~1 MB of bash, zero framework, NASA-grade corpus discipline. Moon-shot quality, built solo.',
    category: 'Runtime',
    repo: 'https://github.com/zUrp-Embedded/LCARS-fleet',
    status: 'wip' as const,
  },
];
---

<Layout title="zUrp Embedded">
  <header class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <img
        src="/logo_zUrp-embedded.png"
        alt="zUrp Embedded corporate logotype"
        class="hero-logo"
      />
      <p class="tagline">Low-tech · DIY · Moon-shot embedded</p>
      <p class="pitch">
        We build embedded systems with the discipline of a space agency and the headcount
        of one developer. Low-tech by conviction, over-engineered by principle.
      </p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="container">
    <section class="catalog">
      <h2>Catalog</h2>
      <div class="grid">
        {products.map((p) => <ProductCard {...p} />)}
      </div>
      <p class="private-note">
        <span class="warn">⚠</span> Active repositories are <strong>private</strong> during
        the forge phase. They will be migrated to this organization on release.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="manifesto">
      <h2>Manifesto</h2>
      <p>
        Agentic orchestration got expensive in 2026. Frameworks grew heavy, abstractions
        grew taxing, and "production-grade" started meaning "dependent on five SaaS
        and a $200/month plan."
      </p>
      <p>
        We went the other way. <span class="mono">LCARS-fleet</span> — <em>Lightweight
        Contained Agent Resilient System</em> — is what you get when you refuse that
        deal: a multi-agent runtime written in ~1&nbsp;MB of plain bash, orchestrated
        around a corpus of specifications reviewed with the rigor of a space program.
        No framework, no magic, no moat. Just files, pipes, and discipline.
      </p>
      <p>
        The name encodes the two load-bearing invariants: the agent is
        <strong>contained</strong> (a wall, not a prompt — nothing escapes the runtime)
        and the system is <strong>resilient</strong> (when the agent fails inside,
        the runtime recovers without human intervention). Everything else is a
        corollary.
      </p>
      <p>
        It's absurd to apply NASA-grade methodology to a solo project. That's the point.
        The sky doesn't care about our budget either.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="charter">
      <h2>Engineering charter</h2>
      <ul class="charter-list">
        <li><strong>Plain text over framework.</strong> Bash, POSIX, files, pipes. If it needs npm, it's not here yet.</li>
        <li><strong>Corpus before code.</strong> Specifications are reviewed before implementation, not after.</li>
        <li><strong>Mechanic over cognitive.</strong> The LLM decides. Bash executes. The boundary is enforced, not suggested.</li>
        <li><strong>One developer, NASA methodology.</strong> 4-phase plan, 11 ADRs, audit pipeline. Overkill is the feature.</li>
        <li><strong>Open by intent.</strong> GPL-3.0 on release. No proprietary hooks.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
    <div class="container footer-inner">
      <p><em>zUrp Embedded — a subsidiary of zUrp Industries.</em></p>
      <p class="legalese">
        Built with <a href="https://astro.build">Astro</a>, ~1&nbsp;MB of bash, and stubbornness.
        Hosted on GitHub Pages because the cloud is just someone else's keiretsu.
      </p>
      <img
        src="/Low_tech_DIY.png"
        alt="Nyan Cat — Low-Tech & DIY internal sticker"
        class="easter-egg"
        title="Internal sticker — culture zUrp"
      />
    </div>
  </footer>
</Layout>

<style>
  .container {
    max-width: 1100px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero {
    background:
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 20% 30%, rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.08) 0%, transparent 50%),
      radial-gradient(ellipse at 80% 70%, rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.04) 0%, transparent 50%),
      var(--bg);
    padding: 6rem 0 5rem;
    text-align: center;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    position: relative;
  }

  .hero::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background-image:
      linear-gradient(rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.03) 1px, transparent 1px),
      linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.03) 1px, transparent 1px);
    background-size: 32px 32px;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .hero .container {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
  }

  .hero-logo {
    max-width: 520px;
    width: 80%;
    filter: invert(1) brightness(1.1);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .tagline {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.2em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .pitch {
    max-width: 620px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
  }

  section {
    padding: 4rem 0;
  }

  section h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    color: var(--fg);
  }

  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .private-note {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    padding: 1rem;
    background: rgba(249, 115, 22, 0.06);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
    border-radius: 3px;
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
  }

  .private-note .warn {
    color: var(--accent);
    margin-right: 0.25rem;
  }

  .manifesto, .charter {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .manifesto p {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
  }

  .mono {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    color: var(--fg);
    font-size: 0.95em;
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    padding: 0.1em 0.4em;
    border-radius: 3px;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .charter-list {
    max-width: 720px;
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .charter-list li {
    padding: 0.75rem 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .charter-list li strong {
    color: var(--fg);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .charter-list li:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  footer {
    background: var(--bg-elev);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding: 3rem 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .footer-inner p {
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .legalese {
    font-size: 0.8rem !important;
    color: var(--fg-muted);
    opacity: 0.7;
  }

  .easter-egg {
    max-width: 140px;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    opacity: 0.6;
    transition: opacity 0.2s ease, transform 0.2s ease;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .easter-egg:hover {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: scale(1.1) rotate(-2deg);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .hero {
      padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
    }
    .hero-logo {
      max-width: 300px;
      width: 90%;
    }
    section {
      padding: 3rem 0;
    }
    section h2 {
      font-size: 1.6rem;
    }
  }
</style>
